Title: A Woman Plays a Stringed Instrument in the Company of Tamed Animals and Birds
Medium: ink and pigments on thin laid paper (probably Kashmiri)
Description: On this folio from Walters manuscript W.626, a woman plays a stringed instrument in the company of tamed animals and birds.
Keywords: Islamic; Book; Codex; Colophon; Illumination; Illustration; Manuscript; India; Sufism; Literature -- Poetry; Literature -- Prose
